# AWS Systems Manager Parameter Store - Secrets Configuration
# 
# This file defines all secrets that will be injected into AWS SSM Parameter Store.
# Copy this file to .env.ssm and replace placeholder values with actual secrets.
#
# Usage:
#   1. Copy: cp .env.ssm.example .env.ssm
#   2. Edit .env.ssm with your actual secrets
#   3. Run: ./scripts/bootstrap/08-inject-ssm-parameters.sh
#
# Format:
#   /path/to/parameter=value
#
# Notes:
#   - All parameters are created as SecureString (encrypted at rest)
#   - Parameters can be updated by running the script again
#   - .env.ssm is gitignored for security

# ============================================================================
# Global LLM API Keys (Shared by all services)
# ============================================================================
# These are platform-wide secrets used by any service that needs LLM access
/zerotouch/prod/openai_api_key=sk-your-openai-api-key-here
/zerotouch/prod/anthropic_api_key=sk-ant-your-anthropic-api-key-here

# ============================================================================
# GitHub Credentials (Shared Across Services)
# ============================================================================

# GitHub Container Registry (GHCR) Credentials
# Used for pulling private container images from ghcr.io
# Generate token at: https://github.com/settings/tokens (with read:packages scope)
/zerotouch/prod/ghcr/username=your-github-username
/zerotouch/prod/ghcr/password=ghp_your_github_personal_access_token

# GitHub Repository Access (for ArgoCD)
# Used by ArgoCD to access private Git repositories (e.g., zerotouch-tenants)
# Generate token at: https://github.com/settings/tokens (with repo scope)
# NOTE: Can use the same token as GHCR if it has both read:packages and repo scopes
/zerotouch/prod/github/username=your-github-username
/zerotouch/prod/github/token=ghp_your_github_personal_access_token

# ============================================================================
# ArgoCD Repository Credentials (for ExternalSecrets)
# ============================================================================
# These credentials are managed by External Secrets Operator (ESO) and stored
# in AWS SSM Parameter Store. ESO automatically creates and syncs Kubernetes
# secrets for ArgoCD repository access.

# Tenant Registry Repository
/zerotouch/prod/argocd/repos/zerotouch-tenants/url=https://github.com/your-org/zerotouch-tenants.git
/zerotouch/prod/argocd/repos/zerotouch-tenants/username=your-github-username
/zerotouch/prod/argocd/repos/zerotouch-tenants/password=ghp_your_github_personal_access_token

# ============================================================================
# Add more tenant repositories following the same pattern:
# /zerotouch/prod/argocd/repos/<tenant-name>/url=https://github.com/org/repo.git
# /zerotouch/prod/argocd/repos/<tenant-name>/username=username
# /zerotouch/prod/argocd/repos/<tenant-name>/password=token
# ============================================================================
